The capture detector is a multiplicity-type
isolated segments of NaI(Tl) crystal. Detector was
divided into two halves, each consisting of 8
segments. The overall dimensions of NaI(Tl) detector
were 30.5 cm diameter and 30.5 cm length with an
8.9-cm diameter through hole along detector axis. Each
segment is hermetically sealed in an aluminum can and
is connected to a photomultiplier tube. The neutron
beam was collimated to a diameter of 4.76 cm. Neutrons
that scatter from the sample are absorbed by a 1.0-cm-
thick hollow cylindrical liner fabricated of 99.4 wt%
10B carbide ceramic to reduce the number of scattered
Neutron energy was determined by time of flight
method. Pulsed electron beam was used.
57-MeV electron beam from the RPI electron
LINAC impinges on a water-cooled tantalum target.
Bare-bounce neutron target (BBT) was used for this
measurement. The tantalum plates are mounted off the
moderator is mounted adjacent to the tantalum plates
and centered on the neutron beam axis.
